						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Genetic-resources-conservation-and-use-in-the-context-of-climate-change-training-opportunity" title="Genetic resources conservation and use in the context of climate change: training opportunity" alt="link">Genetic resources conservation and use in the context of climate change: training opportunity</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Centre for Development Innovation at Wageningen has announced a very interesting and relevant short course on <a href="http://www.cdi.wur.nl/UK/newsagenda/agenda/Contemporay_approaches_in_genetic_resources_conservation_and_use.htm%20" target="_blank">“Contemporary approaches to genetic resources conservation and use in the context of climate change</a>”, with a focus on genetic resource policy and management and integrated seed sector development” to be held 16 April – 4 May 2012. The overall objective of the training programme is to enhance participants’ capabilities to deal with the management of genetic resources activities and programmes. In addition, relevant policies regarding genetic resources will receive special attention. The course programme aims for participants and facilitators to exchange experiences and to enhance understanding of effective approaches towards the conservation and sustainable use of genetic resources in agriculture.</p>
							<p><span class="date">21/09/2011</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/Genetic-resources-conservation-and-use-in-the-context-of-climate-change-training-opportunity">Read more...</a>
