<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/C-V-Raman-International-Fellowship-for-African-Researchers-2011" title="C V Raman International Fellowship for African Researchers 2011" alt="link">C V Raman International Fellowship for African Researchers 2011</a></h2>

	
					<p><b>DEADLINE for Applications: July 31, 2011.</b>C.V. Raman’s scientific achievements are the inspiration for this fellowship program, established in 2010, to promote scientific cooperation through collaborative research with African scholars.Fellowship support includes opportunities for:


Senior experts, scientists and professors

Persons with Ph.D/M.Tech/M.Sc. in Engineering or technical fields, or 6-20 years working experience

Post -Doctoral Fellows


Follow the link below for all information and necessary documents (the flyer and the brochure with application form):<a href="http://www.ficci.com/sector-additional-page.asp?docid=23&amp;secid=35" target="_blank">http://www.ficci.com/sector-additional-page.asp?docid=23&amp;secid=35</a>


African applicants are expected to identify a host institution in India and in the application process submit a letter of intent. The list of approved Science and Technology institutions in India are in the attached brochure. 

The application is included in the attached brochure. African applicants are required to submit an application to the Indian Embassy in their country. We encourage applicants to send copies of the application to USAID missions in Africa and India (email: sross@usaid.gov) for follow-up. 

The Indian Missions in Africa will select candidates and send the application to the Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce in India.


</p>
